        <p>Lost and Found is a service or location where lost items are collected and stored, with the hope of reuniting them with their rightful owners. It could be a physical space like a department or a virtual platform like a website or app.</p>
        <p><b>2. How does Lost and Found work?</b></p>
        <p>When someone finds a lost item, they can turn it in to the Lost and Found facility. The staff will document the item's description, date, and location of discovery. If the owner comes forward, they can claim their lost item by providing necessary identification.</p>
        <p><b>3. Common lost items:</b></p>
